## Tranco List

This folder contains the Tranco top-sites ranking used as an auxiliary reference in this project.

Tranco is a research-oriented top-sites ranking designed to provide a more reliable and manipulation-resistant alternative to traditional website popularity lists. It was proposed in the paper *Tranco: A Research-Oriented Top Sites Ranking Hardened Against Manipulation* and is made available through the official Tranco service.

In this project, the Tranco list is used only as an auxiliary resource for domain-based analysis, benign-domain comparison, filtering strategies and future feature engineering.

## Possible Uses

The Tranco list can support:

- identification of popular domains in benign DNS traffic;
- comparison between queried domains and well-known domains;
- filtering or marking domains that appear in a popularity ranking;
- enrichment of DNS-based features;
- analysis of suspicious, random-looking or low-popularity domains;
- future experiments involving domain popularity as an additional feature.

## Citation

If you use this resource in academic work, cite the original Tranco paper:

```bibtex
@inproceedings{lepochat2019tranco,
  title     = {Tranco: A Research-Oriented Top Sites Ranking Hardened Against Manipulation},
  author    = {Le Pochat, Victor and Van Goethem, Tom and Tajalizadehkhoob, Samaneh and Korczy{\'n}ski, Maciej and Joosen, Wouter},
  booktitle = {Proceedings of the 26th Annual Network and Distributed System Security Symposium (NDSS 2019)},
  year      = {2019},
  doi       = {10.14722/ndss.2019.23386}
}
